    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-11T08:40:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-11T08:40:00-05:00" n="350"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d350">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1608.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">White</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-11T09:00:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 11, 1914, 9 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Horacista party reported not voting Santiago; unless the court again annuls
                    proceedings, Jiménez national majority assured. Horacista tactics are to cavil
                    at elections and to scare people with revolutionary propaganda. Influential
                    Jiménez party are anxious that United States should recognize the validity of
                    elections at once and declare openly they will not tolerate revolutionary
                    activity. This course beneficial if Department is prepared promptly to make good
                    its threats. But I think it would also be well for such declaration to be
                    preceded by formal promise from Jiménez and Velásquez to support financial
                    control. Am credibly informed Arias loyal to Jiménez and not likely to join
                    trouble makers.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
